definitions.definition: A city in the Gisborne Region, North Island , New Zealand , named after William Gisborne .
A region , territorial authority , and unitary authority on the east coast of the North Island of New Zealand , with its headquarters in the city; in full, Gisborne District .
A town in Victoria , Australia , named after Henry Fyshe Gisborne .
